# Now check the JSON output for duplicates
j = d.to_json()
ot_keys = [ot["key"] for ot in j["object_types"]]
print("JSON object_types size:", len(ot_keys))
dups2 = {k: c for k, c in Counter(ot_keys).items() if c > 1}
print("JSON-level dups:", dups2)
'
If dups is empty but dups2 has entries, the SDK emits more than the dict contains — pointing at SDK-level duplication. If both are empty, the duplicate is being introduced by patch-describe-xml.py somehow. Paste outputs.




